			<div class="blog-faq">
				<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What are facial implants and how do they work?</h3>
					<p>Facial implants are biocompatible devices surgically placed over specific facial bones to add volume, projection, and definition. They work by augmenting the underlying bone structure to improve facial proportions and balance. Common areas treated include the chin, cheeks, and jawline. The implants are placed through small incisions and sit beneath the tissues, enhancing the natural contours of the face for a more harmonious appearance.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long do facial implant results last?</h3>
					<p>Facial implant results are permanent. Unlike dermal fillers that require repeated treatments, facial implants provide lasting enhancement that does not diminish over time. Once the implants have fully healed and settled into position, they remain stable for life. Most patients enjoy their improved facial balance for decades without the need for replacement, though individual outcomes may vary.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Will facial implants look natural?</h3>
					<p>When performed by an experienced board-certified plastic surgeon like Dr. Johar, facial implants produce natural-looking results. The implants are placed beneath the tissues to augment the bone structure rather than sitting visibly on the surface. The size and shape of each implant are carefully selected to complement the patient's existing facial features, ensuring that the enhancement looks proportionate and organic rather than artificial.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What is the recovery time after facial implant surgery?</h3>
					<p>Most patients return to work and social activities within one to two weeks after facial implant surgery. Swelling and bruising are typically most prominent during the first three to five days and subside significantly within two weeks. Strenuous exercise should be avoided for four to six weeks. Final results become fully apparent within three to six months as all residual swelling resolves and the tissues adapt to the implants.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can I combine facial implants with other procedures?</h3>
					<p>Yes, facial implants are frequently combined with other procedures for comprehensive facial rejuvenation. Common combinations include rhinoplasty, facelift, eyelid surgery, and fat grafting. Combining procedures can be more cost-effective and allow for a single recovery period. During your consultation, Dr. Johar will discuss which combination of procedures will best achieve your aesthetic goals.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Are facial implant procedures painful?</h3>
					<p>Most patients report that facial implant surgery is less painful than expected. The procedure is performed under anesthesia, so there is no discomfort during surgery. Afterward, prescribed pain medications effectively manage any soreness during the first few days. By the end of the first week, most patients have significantly reduced their pain medication usage and feel relatively comfortable.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Who is a good candidate for facial implants?</h3>
					<p>Good candidates for facial implants are healthy adults who have realistic expectations and desire permanent improvement to facial balance. They should be concerned about a weak chin, flat cheekbones, or an undefined jawline. Non-smokers or those willing to quit before surgery are preferred, as smoking impairs healing. During your consultation, Dr. Johar will evaluate your facial anatomy and goals to determine if facial implants are the right option for you.</p>
